{
  "abstract": "Alfisols are agriculturally important soils throughout\r\nmuch of the semi-arid tropics (SAT) in spite of\r\nserious physical and chemical limitations. They are\r\nthe t h i r d most important soil order in the world, covering\r\n13.1% of the world area (Buringh, 1982) and a r e\r\nthe most abundant s o i l s i n t h e SAT, cover nearly 16%\r\nof the tropics and 33% of the SAT region.",
